This also looks quite logical, but it is less efective than against ...Be6. } 14... Rxd1+ 15. Rxd1 { The most natural recapture, but now the bishop on h3 is not defended so g5 is not a threat. } 15... Be6 16. Rh1 $6 { Logical, but not effective, because Black has enough time to remove the knight on f6 and neutralize White's play. } 16... Nd7 $15 { [%cal Ba6a5,Ba5a4,Bd7b6]Black attack is faster. Ideas: a5-a4 and Nb6 in case white removes the queen from f2. } * 

