This was given by Negi as their main move. This move threatens Bb6. } 14... Rb8 { We stop the threat and improve our rook. } 15. h5 Be6 $1 { We complete development and point the bishop towards White's queenside. } 16. g5 Nd7 17. f4 $6 { This is natural, but gives Black a very big initiative. } 17... exf4 18. Bxf4 Qa5 $1 19. Bxb8 Rxb8 $17 { [%cal Gb5b4,Gd7e5,Ge7c5]Black is much better in this position. In addition to absolute dominance over the dark squares, which alone would compensate for the exchange, Black also has a strong attack on White's king. } * 

