is position. Our bishop on d5 is very strong and it restricts the knight on a5. Our plan is to generate counterplay on the kingside with moves like ...f5, ...h6 & ...g5 next. } 20. Rb1 Kd7 $1 { The b7-square is covered, so the king is better placed in the center for the endgame than on g8 after. We also have plans with counterplay related to ...g5. } 21. Ke2 f5 $1 { [%cal Gg7g5,Gh7h6]We implement our plan. Black is completely fine in this endgame. A famous example went... } 22. Rb6 g5 $1 23. fxg5 Rhg8 $37 { Black had an initiative and managed to win in 0-1 Volokitin, A -Giri, A Germany, 2013. } * 

