sions. White allows Black to save their pawn, but avoids the b6 theme we see in the 18.O-O-O (See the corresponding variation from the PGN) variation. } 18... b5 19. Ke2 Ke7 $5 { The easiest. We just want to push ...f5 next move. } 20. Rbd1 f5 21. exf6+ gxf6 $10 { Black now has counterplay thanks to the semi-open g-file and good minor pieces, as was played in ½-½ Frolyanov, D - Wang, Y Sochi, 2015. The endgame is equal. } * 

