1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 { The starting position of the Taimanov. } 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. Be3 { The English Attack, White's most ambitious and critical attempt. White typically plays Qd2, O-O-O, and f3 next. They go for a quick pawn storm on the kingside; one key motif is g4-g5. } 6... a6 7. Qd2 Nf6 { Some years ago, there were some players that started to experiment with 7...Be7!? because of the 8.f4 try that we are going to analyze. However, if White is ready for it, in the end he has more flexibility and the subtlety can backfire. } ( 7... Be7 { The idea is to avoid some sidelines and transpose to the main line, however, it also allows several unpleasant possibilities: } ) 8. f4 { Creates the positional threat of e4-e5, so Black has to take action immediately. } 8... Bb4 { Now that f3 is not possible, this is the best move, putting pressure on e4. } 9. Bd3 { Tha main move, defending e4. } 9... Na5 { [%cal Ga5c4]I have tried to make other moves work, but this is simply the most reliable. We want to play ...Nc4 and prepare ...Bxc3 in the meantime. } 10. a3 Bxc3 11. Qxc3 Qxc3+ 12. bxc3 d5 $1 { It is necessary to fight for the e4 and c4 central light squares. Now our bishop can also be developed. } 13. exd5 { The most critical line, revitalized by Carlsen with his win against Matlakov in Tata Steel back in 2018. } 13... exd5 $1 { It is key to recapture with the pawn. It controls the important light squares c4 and e4. } ( 13... Nxd5 $2 $146 { Capturing with the knight on d5 doesn't solve all of Black's problems. } 14. Bd2 { The problem is our knights lack good outposts. The c4-square is still weak, but we cannot take advantage of it. For example : } 14... Nb6 $146 15. Rb1 Nbc4 $146 { it looks like we have managed to get our knights to good squares. If we had one more tempo in, with ....Bd7 already played, we would be fine. But after the concrete } 16. Rb4 Nxd2 $146 17. Kxd2 { We are very passive. White is the one that is going to get first to the open files, and the endgame is just too unpleasant. } ) 14. O-O O-O 15. Rfe1 Ne4 { [%cal Gc8d7,Ga8c8,Ga5c4]Black does not have any problems, now our king is very safe. We are going to finish development with ...Bd7, ...Nc4, ...Rfe8, ...Rac8 with equal chances. } * 

