1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 { The starting position of the Taimanov. } 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. Be3 { The English Attack, White's most ambitious and critical attempt. White typically plays Qd2, O-O-O, and f3 next. They go for a quick pawn storm on the kingside; one key motif is g4-g5. } 6... a6 7. Qf3 { White's queen is coming to g3 – either immediately to invite a queen trade and head for an endgame ( } 7... b5 $5 ( 7... b5 $2 8. Qg3 $2 { ), or later, after luring our queen to c6 with 7. Qf3 7...b5 8.Nxc6 Qxc6 9.Bd3 Ba3 10.Nd1 Bb4+ 11.c3 Be7 12.Qg3 , targeting our soft spot on g7. } ) 8. Qg3 $5 { This is the most solid line for White, entering an endgame where he has some pressure thanks to the semi-open h-file and active pieces. But as we will see, Black has no issues in the endgame if he understands the typical plans and correct piece placement. } 8... Qxg3 9. hxg3 Nxd4 10. Bxd4 Bb7 11. f3 { The strongest move, because we were threatening b4 taking the pawn on e4. 11.O-O-O would actually transpose to the imprecise 8.O-O-O (See the corresponding variation from the PGN). } 11... Ne7 12. O-O-O Nc6 13. Be3 Bb4 14. g4 { The most critical movement, trying to put the pawn on g5 and fix our kingside structure. } 14... f6 $1 { It is not necessary to take on c3 yet. We can't allow g5, making this thematic move necessary. } ( 14... Bxc3 $2 15. bxc3 { we would have very weak dark squares. } ) 15. g5 { White continues their plan. } 15... fxg5 16. Bxg5 h5 $1 { I really like this move, as it expands our control on the kingside. Our idea is to exchange the g5-bishop, put the knight on e5 and push the kingside pawns. We have more pawn islands than White, so our structure is a little bit worse, but we will have counterplay on both sides as compensation. It is difficult to analyze the endgame concretely, we try to give some sample lines to give you a feel for this type of endgame. } ( 16... Ne5 $2 $146 17. Be3 Nf7 $2 $146 { Bringing the knight to f7 immediately is also perfectly playable. } ) 17. Be3 $1 { The strongest move, though difficult for a human to find. This deep prophylactic move is intended to counter ...Be7, which now doesn't come with tempo. } 17... Rc8 $133 { [%cal Gc6e5,Gb4e7,Gg7g5]Black's position still looks very decent to me, and with many pieces still on the board, there's plenty of opportunity to outplay the opponent. } * 

