the knight on h5! White should improve the knight on d1 if they want to continue to fight for the initiative, and they can do so while exchanging light-squared bishops by including Be4. } 16. Nf2 Qc7 $1 { Threatening the pawn on e5. } 17. O-O { This indirectly defends the pawn. } 17... d6 $1 { The best move. Once the pawn on e5 dissapears, the knight can safely come back to f6. } 18. exd6 Bxd6 $133 { [%cal Gh5f4,Ge8g8]This complex position seems around equal, we have good pieces but we will need some care on the kingisde with the holes on the dark squares. Probably the knight will go to f4. } * 

