ge. } 16... Nxc3 17. a3 Ba5 18. g6 { The engine's idea, generating counterplay on the kingside. We are still more than fine with our extra material. } 18... Ne4+ 19. b4 Bb6 20. gxf7+ Qxf7 $37 { [%cal Gc8d7,Ge8c8]In order to restore the material balance, White will have to give up the bishop pair by playing Bg2-Bxe4. Black will proceed with ...Bd7 and ...O-O-O with a great position. } * 

