 been tried, but I find this the most reliable one, forcing matters on the center. } 12. exd5 cxd5 13. Bd4 Bb7 $1 { A strong pawn sacrifice. Finishing development is more important than the pawn on f6. Also, after giving away their dark-squared bishop, White's firepower gets reduced significantly. } 14. h4 { This looks natural, but thanks to developing quickly with ...Bb7 we can get enough counterplay just in time. } 14... Rc8 15. Qe2 Kf8 $1 { Now g5 loses a lot of strength. } 16. g5 $6 hxg5 17. hxg5 Nd7 $15 { [%cal Ge6e5,Gh8h2]White's position is starting to look very dangerous. We are actually better on all sides of the board! } * 

