 been tried, but I find this the most reliable one, forcing matters on the center. } 12. exd5 cxd5 13. Bd4 Bb7 $1 { A strong pawn sacrifice. Finishing development is more important than the pawn on f6. Also, after giving away their dark-squared bishop, White's firepower gets reduced significantly. } 14. g5 $1 hxg5 15. Rxg5 Qxh2 16. Rxg7 { White's most natural move. } 16... Qh6+ $1 { Otherwise we would be lost. } 17. Kb1 Qxg7 18. Bxf6 Qh6 19. Bxh8 Qxh8 20. Ne2 Bd6 $13 { Another typical position for this line, that the engines usually evaluate too optimistically for White in my opinion, because they are just extremely good at finding every possible little tactic when they have an initiative! This style is not really possible to replicate for human players, and with the bishop pair and a strong center, I feel confident about Black's chances. } * 

