1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 { The starting position of the Taimanov. } 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. Be3 { The English Attack, White's most ambitious and critical attempt. White typically plays Qd2, O-O-O, and f3 next. They go for a quick pawn storm on the kingside; one key motif is g4-g5. } 6... a6 7. g4 h6 $5 { I like to recommend this rare move, which I feel still has a lot of unexplored potential. The point is to slow down g5 and give Black's knight a safe square on f6 if possible. In general, it leads to less forced play and gives White more chances to make mistakes in the early stages, especially if they are not very familiar with the line. } ( 7... b5 8. Nxc6 $146 Qxc6 9. Qd2 { The pawn sacrifice that brought 7.g4 into the spotlight. } 9... b4 10. Ne2 $146 Qxe4 11. Rg1 { This position has been played by very strong players over the last three years and has developed an enormous amount of theory. Black is probably fine with ultra-precise play, but White is usually extremely well-prepared, and the style of play is too forced for my taste. } ) 8. h4 { This is White's most logical move, expanding further on the kingside. } 8... Nf6 $1 { This is strong now that White cannot play g5. The next move we would like to play is ...Bb4. } 9. Nxc6 { An uncomfortable move to face. In many lines, ...Ne5 provides us with a lot of counterplay, but this move denies us that possibility. } 9... Qxc6 $1 { The correct reaction, we need our queen to make contact with the c3-knight and the e4-pawn to get counterplay. } 10. Qf3 $6 { White wants to push g5 and take on h1 with the queen. The problem for him is we get a lot of play on the queenside with a typical resource. } 10... Ba3 { I like this theme that will also been seen in the table. We force White to make a concession. } 11. Bd4 { This is an interesting pawn sacrifice, but not dangerous from an objective point of view. } 11... Bxb2 12. Rb1 Bxc3+ 13. Bxc3 Nxe4 14. Bxg7 Rg8 15. Bxh6 b5 $13 { [%cal Gc8b7,Ga8c8,Gg8g6,Gg6f6][%csl Re1]Material is equal and White has the bishop pair, but Black has good chances because our king is safer. } * 

