e3 Bxb2 16. Bxh7+ $3 { This is the key difference with respect to 14.Be3! } 16... Kxh7 17. Qh5+ Kg8 18. c3 $3 { Only move to win. The lines are very beautiful. } 18... Bxa1 19. Qg4+ Kh7 20. Rf3 ) 15. Rf3 { White does not really have sufficient attack on the kingisde, but the rook is better placed on f3 than on f1. We continue development. } 15... Bd7 16. Rg3 Kh8 { [%cal Gf8g8,Ge6e5,Gb8d8,Gg7f6][%csl Yb2,Rc1]Getting out of the pin. Black has good play and White has still not solved the development issues on the queenside. } 17. Bf1 Bf6 18. a4 Rg8 19. c3 Rxg3 20. hxg3 Qg8 { [%cal Gg8g7,Gc6a5,Ga5c4,Ga8g8]Black has sufficient counterplay. } * 

