e3 Bxb2 16. Bxh7+ $3 { This is the key difference with respect to 14.Be3! } 16... Kxh7 17. Qh5+ Kg8 18. c3 $3 { Only move to win. The lines are very beautiful. } 18... Bxa1 19. Qg4+ Kh7 20. Rf3 ) 15. c3 { This is more dangerous with Bd3 included, so we need to be careful. } 15... bxc3 16. bxc3 { [%cal Gc1e3]The correct capture, keeping control over dark squares in the center. } ( 16. Nxc3 $2 $146 Bd7 $15 ) 16... Nb4 $1 { Black has to act quickly! This is an improvement over Aronian and Bacrot games, although to be fair they were blitz and rapid. } ( 16... Bd7 17. Be3 Rf7 18. Qe2 $14 { ½–½ Dominguez Perez-Aronian, Titled Tuesday 2024, is uncomfortable for Black, as Leinier Dominguez showed against Aronian. Black is slightly cramped, and it is not easy to exchange our bad bishop on d7. } ) 17. Be2 Nxa2 $1 { This looks dangerous but works tactically! } 18. Bb2 ( 18. Qc2 $2 Nxc3 $146 ) 18... Bd7 { Black is fine. } 19. Qb3 Bxb5 20. Bxb5 Qc7 $133 { [%cal Ga2c3,Gc7c5]White cannot win our knight. } * 

