y improvement over the line: } ( 11... Rb8 12. b3 O-O 13. Qg3 Nd7 $146 14. Na4 $146 c5 15. f5 Bf6 16. Rad1 { White has a lot of pressure on the d6-pawn. } ) 12. Qg3 a5 13. Kh1 { Always useful, this move prepares central action. } 13... Nd7 $1 { This is different from Kollars game: with the knight still on c3, White is not able to take advantage of our weak d6-pawn. } 14. f5 Bf6 15. Rad1 Be5 16. Bf4 exf5 17. exf5 f6 $13 { [%cal Gd6d5]Black is very solid and ready to push the pawns in the center. } * 

