 { This idea is a novelty, but it has some venom and we should check it. } 13... exf4 $1 { The safest move. } ( 13... Bxg4 14. Bxg4 Nxg4 $146 15. Nd5 $146 Qd7 16. f5 $36 { looks quite dangerous for Black. } ) 14. g5 $5 fxe3 15. gxf6 Bxf6 16. Nd5 Qd8 17. Nxf6+ gxf6 18. Qxe3 Kh8 { [%cal Gf8g8,Gg8g6,Gc8e6]Our structure is quite ugly, but we are a pawn up at the moment and it can be argued that we have the safer king. Equality seems like a fair assessment from Stockfish! } 19. Qd4 Rg8+ 20. Kh1 Rg6 21. Bh5 ( 21. Rad1 $2 Bh3 $16 ) 21... Rh6 22. Bxf7 Qe7 23. Bd5 Be6 $10 { We give back the pawn to complete development and neutralize White's bishop. } * 

