. b5 $2 12. Nxc6 $146 Qxc6 13. e5 $16 ) 12. Bxd4 b5 13. a3 { The most popular move by a lot of margin: avoiding ...b4 is useful for White. } 13... Bb7 { The main tabiya of the 10.Qe1 complex: we should understand this position very well! Harikhrisna devotes a lot of attention to it in his incredible Taimanov course. Here, we will play slightly different lines. Our main idea is playing ...Ne8 & ...Bf6 as fast as we can to neutralize White's active bishop and slow down their attack on the kingside. However, we cannot play it against all moves and I warn you that my approach is move by move, so you should know the theory really well! } 14. Bf3 Rad8 15. Kh1 Ne8 16. Rad1 Bf6 $1 { This is very similar to the 14.Kh1 (See the corresponding variation from the PGN) lines. Black is completely fine. } * 

