1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 { The starting position of the Taimanov. } 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. g3 { g3 will never go out of fashion against the Taimanov. It is quite solid for White, and Bf4 can be an idea in some variations. } 6... a6 { It is important to start with this move, as } ( 6... Nf6 $146 { gives White some extra Nb5 ideas. } ) 7. Bg2 Nf6 8. O-O Nxd4 { This is the best move without a doubt, Nxc6 ideas can be quite uncomfortable in the g3 line. } ( 8... d6 { also thought of reccomending this move, trying to get us into Scheveningen territory, but White has the unpleasant plan } 9. Nxc6 $146 bxc6 10. Na4 $146 { As Carlsen showed against Rapport, this kind of position can be quite unpleasant. } ) ( 8... Bc5 { This is the most natural reaction, but as we said earlier Black faces some problems after } 9. Nxc6 $146 dxc6 10. Na4 $146 Ba7 11. c4 { The key move. According to the machine White's advantage is not too big, but our dark square bishop is bad and I think in practice it is not a good position. } 11... b5 12. e5 { The big point. Everything works for White. } 12... Nd7 $146 13. Nc3 $146 Nxe5 $146 14. Bf4 ) 9. Qxd4 Bc5 10. Qd3 Ng4 $1 { Very nice and also quite typical. The e5-square is very good, and we also put pressure on the f2-pawn. } 11. Qe2 { The most common move, alternatives are not too dangerous, but I recommend you still take a look at them because the resulting positions are quite typical for these lines and can improve your Sicilian middlegames. } 11... h5 $1 { Increasing pressure on White's position. The g3-pawn serves as a hook, providing us with counterplay. } 12. e5 $5 { A dangerous idea. The e5-square is very good for our knight, and the bishop on g2 is very passive with a pawn on e4, so White sacrifices a pawn to open a line for their pieces. } 12... Nxe5 13. Bf4 f6 $1 ( 13... d6 { is worse, the pawn becomes weak after a potential Ne4. } ) 14. Ne4 Be7 $13 { [%cal Gh5h4,Gd7d5]The position is quite complex, but at the moment we are a pawn up and thanks to the precise 13...f6, we remain solid. Ideas: ...h4 & ...d5 followed by ...Qc4. } * 

