1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 { The starting position of the Taimanov. } 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. g3 { g3 will never go out of fashion against the Taimanov. It is quite solid for White, and Bf4 can be an idea in some variations. } 6... a6 { It is important to start with this move, as } ( 6... Nf6 $146 { gives White some extra Nb5 ideas. } ) 7. Bg2 Nf6 8. O-O Nxd4 { This is the best move without a doubt, Nxc6 ideas can be quite uncomfortable in the g3 line. } ( 8... d6 { also thought of reccomending this move, trying to get us into Scheveningen territory, but White has the unpleasant plan } 9. Nxc6 $146 bxc6 10. Na4 $146 { As Carlsen showed against Rapport, this kind of position can be quite unpleasant. } ) ( 8... Bc5 { This is the most natural reaction, but as we said earlier Black faces some problems after } 9. Nxc6 $146 dxc6 10. Na4 $146 Ba7 11. c4 { The key move. According to the machine White's advantage is not too big, but our dark square bishop is bad and I think in practice it is not a good position. } 11... b5 12. e5 { The big point. Everything works for White. } 12... Nd7 $146 13. Nc3 $146 Nxe5 $146 14. Bf4 ) 9. Qxd4 Bc5 10. Qd1 { After } ( 10. Qd3 Ng4 $146 { , White usually has to move the queen again, so he chooses the more modest d1-square for their queen. } ) 10... d6 11. Na4 { If White wants to force us to play e5, this is probably their best chance. } 11... Ba7 12. Bf4 e5 13. Bg5 { Usually White being able to play Bg5 means trouble for Black, but we can get away with it because the knight on a4 is misplaced. } 13... Qd8 ( 13... Ng4 $2 $146 { is also possible, and is something that you can investigate if you want something sharper, but I think keeping things simple against these sidelines is the most intelligent approach. } ) 14. Nc3 h6 15. Bxf6 Qxf6 { We do not want to ruin our pawn structure. } 16. Qd3 Qd8 { We do not want to be exposed after Nd5. } 17. Rad1 Be6 $5 { Developing a piece, since the pawn on d6 is poisoned. } 18. Qxd6 $6 Qxd6 19. Rxd6 Bd4 $15 { [%csl Rd6]And the rook is trapped! ...Ke7 is coming. This is another version where Black sacrifices a pawn with excellent compensation. Actually, White is also losing an exchange by force! } * 

