1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 { The starting position of the Taimanov. } 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. f4 { An old line. 6.f4 looks flexible and aggressive, supporting e5 or a pawn storm, but it weakens the g1-a7 diagonal too much, and we should be very happy to see it. } 6... a6 ( 6... Nxd4 $146 7. Qxd4 b6 { was an interesting suggestion by Pavlidis to confuse the White player, but it is now quite well-known and has lost some of its charm. One of the most dangerous setups for White is } 8. Bd3 Bb7 9. Qf2 $2 { ↑ . White's position is very easy to play, and it's fairly clear that we would prefer the queenside pawns on a6 and b5 rather than a7 and b6. } ) 7. Nxc6 bxc6 { This is the most reliable move in my opinion, although } ( 7... Qxc6 { is also possible. } ) 8. Bd3 { The most natural move and the most commonly played one. } 8... d5 9. O-O ( 9. Be3 { transposes to 8.Be3. (See the corresponding variation from the PGN) } ) 9... Nf6 10. Qe2 { The most logical square for White's queen. } 10... Be7 { The main tabiya of the 6.f4-7.Nxc6 line. Now, Black has several decent moves. } 11. Kh1 { A useful move in general. Black can easily equalize with normal moves like ...O-O, ...Bb7, and ...c5 because White's attack isn't very strong in these lines. However, I want to present a powerful novelty here. } 11... h5 { I like this move a lot. The idea is that after our knight goes to g4, we can sometimes sacrifice it after h3, because with the king on h1 and the open g1-a7 diagonal, we get a lot of play. } 12. e5 Ng4 13. h3 c5 $1 14. hxg4 { The most critical line, accepting the piece. } 14... hxg4+ 15. Kg1 Bb7 $1 { [%cal Gc5c4]We can even play in a slow way. We develop our bishop to its best square before pushing the desired c4. } ( 15... c4 { is not so precise, because after } 16. Be3 cxd3 17. cxd3 d4 18. Bxd4 Bb7 19. Ne4 $36 $146 { , Black does not have time for queenside castling as in the main line. } ) 16. Qxg4 c4 17. Be2 $2 { If White is greedy, they get a completely lost position. } 17... Qb6+ 18. Rf2 O-O-O $19 { [%cal Gh8h4,Gd8h8,Ge7c5]Black's attack breaks through. } * 

