1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 { The starting position of the Taimanov. } 5. Nc3 Qc7 6. Bg5 $5 { A strange idea that has been tried a couple of times by Paravyan, a dangerous theoretician. We don't need to know much, but it is useful to be aware of the pawn sacrifice in the main line. } 6... Nf6 7. Ndb5 $6 Qb8 8. Bxf6 gxf6 9. g3 { This was tried by Sedlak, a strong GM, once, but it's simply not very good. } 9... Bc5 $15 { It is clear that Black's bishop pair is the main factor, and White's knight on b5 is stranded. } * 

