ral dangerous continuations like } 12. Nc3 $2 $146 Nxc3 $146 13. bxc3 $40 { . } ) 12. Nf3 b5 $5 { This can also be tried in case we are not happy with a repetition. The main idea is } 13. Bxd5 ( 13. Bxb5 Qb6 14. Qe2 Bxf2+ { , which leads to double-edged play. } ) 13... Qxd5 14. Qxd5 exd5 15. Be3 Rd8 { In this endgame, we have got enough counterplay to compensate for our weak d5-pawn. } 16. Bxc5 Nxc5 17. Nd4 Nd3 18. Re2 b4 $133 { [%cal Ga7a5,Gc8b7]Black is fine. The plan is to continue with ...a5 followed by ...Ba6. } * 

