ite dangerous. White wants to attack our weak king. } 16... Rfc8 { Why to bring the rook here? On d8 it is exposed to Bg5 and clearly our target is the c3-pawn. We leave the f8-square free for the bishop in order to come for defensive tasks. } 17. Rg3 g6 $13 { [%cal Gc5f8,Gf8g7]A strong defensive move. ...Bf8-g7 is a very good plan, giving our king a much-needed defender. } * 

