1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 { The starting position of the Taimanov. } 5. c4 Nf6 6. Nxc6 { This is rarely played, but it is actually a little tricky against our repertoire. } 6... dxc6 $5 { I feel this is worth the risk. } ( 6... bxc6 { is much more solid, but this move gives us good chances, because White has to walk a narrow path not to be worse. } ) 7. Qxd8+ Kxd8 8. e5 ( 8. Nc3 $2 $146 e5 $15 { The d4-weakness gives us a better game. } ) 8... Ng4 9. f4 Bc5 { [%cal Gg4f2,Gg4e3]} 10. h3 $2 { This has been played, trying to create an escape square on h2, but it weakens the dark squares, and it is not very good. } 10... Ne3 $1 { [%csl Rc2]} 11. Bxe3 { After } ( 11. Bd3 Nxg2+ $146 { , our knight can escape via h4. } ) 11... Bxe3 12. g3 g5 $17 { White's center is crumbling and Black was much better in 0-1 Kozhuharov, S - Rusev, K Plovdiv, 2003. } * 

