1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. b4 { A slightly different version of the Wing Gambit with 2. b4 that we should take a look at because we play with a quick ...d5 there. I like a different approach, taking advantage that the pawn on b4 is now defended. } 3... cxb4 4. a3 Nf6 $1 { A strong move. The knight will be safe on d5 momentarily, because the pawn on b4 helps avoid c4. If White takes on b4, then we can develop our bishop with tempo. } 5. e5 { The only decent move to try and develop an initiative. } 5... Nd5 6. Bc4 { This is not too good; we can exchange White's pawn. } 6... d6 $17 { Black is a pawn up and has easy development. } * 

