1. e4 c5 2. c4 { Weakening the d4-square cannot be good. } 2... Nc6 3. Nc3 g6 { The same moves we play against the Closed Sicilian. With the pawn on c4, ...g6 makes even more sense. } 4. g3 Bg7 5. Bg2 a6 $1 { We want White to play the weakening a4. } 6. Nge2 Rb8 { Starting with } ( 6... b5 $2 { is also possible, as we get a very good version of the Benko gambit after } 7. cxb5 axb5 8. Nxb5 $146 Ba6 { . } ) 7. O-O b5 8. d3 d6 9. f4 Bd7 $15 { We have a nice version of the closed Sicilian. Next ...e6, ...Nge7, ...O-O, & ...f5 look like a very decent plan. } * 

