1. e4 c5 2. a3 { Not very impressive. White wants to play b4, so we are going to play with ...g6 to bother him. } 2... g6 3. b4 { The logical continuation. } 3... Bg7 4. Nc3 d6 5. g3 { The most common move. } 5... Nc6 { Hitting the pawn on b4. } 6. Rb1 ( 6. b5 Nd4 $146 { is of course fine for us. } ) 6... Nf6 7. Bg2 cxb4 8. axb4 Bg4 $1 { Typical move when White fianchettos the bishop, because f3 blocks the bishop. } 9. Nge2 Nd4 { [%csl Gf3]Quite unpleasant for White. } * 

