1. e4 c5 2. Na3 { This has been played by some strong players. It is playable, but White cannot fight for an advantage like this, and Black can equalize in various ways. } 2... Nc6 { I chose this one, it seems the easiest. } 3. Bb5 d5 $5 { The most principled, exploiting the fact that our queen cannot be hit by Nc3 moves once we recapture on d5. } 4. Qe2 e6 5. Nf3 a6 6. Bxc6+ bxc6 { [%cal Gg8e7,Ge7g6,Gf8e7,Ge8g8]With the knight on c3, White would have ideas of Na4, b3, & Ba3, but here the knight is clearly misplaced and we have very comfortable play. } * 

