1. e4 c5 2. f4 { This move is sometimes seen at club level, but it allows 2... d5. } 2... d5 { We directly strike in the center. If the position gets opened, White could have a weak kingside due to the f4-pawn. } 3. exd5 { The main move. } 3... Nf6 { Recapturing with the knight is more harmonious than taking with the queen. } 4. c4 { is worse here with the light-squared bishops still on the board. } 4... e6 5. dxe6 Bxe6 { [%cal Gb8c6,Gf8d6,Gd8c7,Ge8c8][%csl Rc4,Rd2,Rf4]This position is just terrible for White: they have a lot of weaknesses, and we also have an advantage in development. } * 

[Event "Lifetime Repertoires: Cuenca's Taimanov Sicilian"]
[Site "2.f4 McDonnell Attack #2"]
