[Black "35) Rare 2nd Moves"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. f4 { This move is sometimes seen at club level, but it allows 2... d5. } 2... d5 { We directly strike in the center. If the position gets opened, White could have a weak kingside due to the f4-pawn. } 3. exd5 { The main move. } 3... Nf6 { Recapturing with the knight is more harmonious than taking with the queen. } 4. Bb5+ { This is the main move. } 4... Bd7 5. Bxd7+ Qxd7 6. c4 { White needs to protect the pawn, otherwise they have nothing to show for their weakened position. } 6... e6 { Again, we want to open the position to exploit White's weaknesses. } 7. dxe6 Qxe6+ 8. Qe2 Qxe2+ { Our compensation for the pawn is of a positional nature, so we do not mind exchanging queens. } 9. Nxe2 Nc6 10. O-O O-O-O { [%cal Gg7g6,Gf8g7,Gc6b4]It is very difficult for White to develop the pieces with all the weaknesses. We will keep improving our position with moves like ...g6, ...Bg7, ...Rhe8, & ...Nb4, and there is no way for White to untangle their position. } * 

