1. e4 c5 2. f4 { This move is sometimes seen at club level, but it allows 2... d5. } 2... d5 { We directly strike in the center. If the position gets opened, White could have a weak kingside due to the f4-pawn. } 3. exd5 { The main move. } 3... Nf6 { Recapturing with the knight is more harmonious than taking with the queen. } 4. Bb5+ { This is the main move. } 4... Bd7 5. Bxd7+ Qxd7 6. c4 { White needs to protect the pawn, otherwise they have nothing to show for their weakened position. } 6... e6 { Again, we want to open the position to exploit White's weaknesses. } 7. Nf3 exd5 8. Ne5 Qc7 { [%cal Gf8d6,Ge8g8]We have recovered the pawn, and we are doing absolutely fine. } * 

